The paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks to predict the most compressible direction of a 360{\deg} video, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to learn associations between visual content and compressibility, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of video codecs, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
